LAGOS – Victor Ayara, former news anchor with Silverbird Tele­vision, has joined in the call for public assistance for one Ofonime Lawson Ifik, whom physicians at Renal Dialysis Centre, Ikeja, Lagos, said requires kidney transplant estimated to cost N11 million. Ayara, who was awarded the Newscaster of the Year by the Nigerian Media Merit Award (NMMA) in its 2010 edition, sent the Save Our Soul (SOS) message in a state­ment he personally endorsed and made available to Sunday INDEPENDENT on Saturday. The Nigerian ace broad­caster and event compere, currently plying his trade in the United States, where he resides, made reference to Sunday INDEPENDENT report of January 30, which reported a similar message earlier released by the Renal Dialysis Centre, the facility managing Lawson’s kidney disease. Osun Guber: Let’s Close Ranks And Eschew Bitterness,… Ojokoro LCDA Chairman Budgets N3.8bn For 2022 Urging the public to reach out to the patient, Ayara pro­vided Lawson’s personal con­tact thus: Phone: 08105805661; Bank: Access Bank Account No: 1532175918. Name: Ofonime Lawson Ifik.